<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Tools on MCP Toolbox for Databases</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/bigtable/tools/</link><description>Recent content in Tools on MCP Toolbox for Databases</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/bigtable/tools/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>bigtable-sql</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/bigtable/tools/bigtable-sql/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/bigtable/tools/bigtable-sql/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about"&gt;About&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;bigtable-sql&lt;/code&gt; tool executes a pre-defined SQL statement against a Bigtable
instance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="googlesql"&gt;GoogleSQL&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bigtable supports SQL queries. The integration with Toolbox supports &lt;code&gt;googlesql&lt;/code&gt;
dialect, the specified SQL statement is executed as a &lt;a href="https://cloud.google.com/bigtable/docs/googlesql-overview"&gt;data manipulation
language (DML)&lt;/a&gt; statements, and specified parameters will
inserted according to their name: e.g. &lt;code&gt;@name&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
